    <item>
      <title>Re: Lore in Monster Missions...</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Lore&amp;message.id=11028#M11028</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;The monster missions are told most often from the perspective of the npc who gives it (in most cases).&amp;nbsp; There are a lot of dialogues where the npc describes their version of history and invites you to take part in it.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We try to be accurate in a lot of them, but not all of them are that way.&amp;nbsp; We don't want to create a situation where players will assume that a monster mission is always "the way it happened."&amp;nbsp; We want to be able to use monster missions to show all kinds of different viewpoints, alternative outcomes, dreams, etc.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What the monster missions&amp;nbsp;also do is cause folks like yourselves to do the research and&amp;nbsp;find the stories in the game to determine how well the missions stack up.&amp;nbsp; That's an outcome I really enjoy the most. :smileyhappy:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Vahlar&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
