      <title>Re: Of the Freeport Militia and other new and odd titles...</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Lore&amp;message.id=10042#M10042</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We added a method for players to adjust their faction in Freeport if they chose to so they could run around the city without being attacked, etc.&amp;nbsp; We also put in Militia/Followers of Marr missions in the city so you could max/minimize your faction with either side.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;That NPC you mention is the one that guides you to the various quests or missions based on&amp;nbsp;your level and your faction.&amp;nbsp; There's a citizens of Freeport faction that allows you to run about the city too.&amp;nbsp; When you become an ally with the Militia or the Followers of Marr, you are granted a title that shows your allegiance.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So, that's where that came from!&lt;/P&gt;</description>
