    <item>
      <title>Re: Taelosia - truth or fiction?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Lore&amp;message.id=9852#M9852</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;This is gonna look like gross self-promotion, but this will be published in some form on our web site in the near future.&amp;nbsp; However, becuase I lub you all so much, I thought it was relevant to post it.&amp;nbsp; And, remember, poor Vahlar is dead in the end zone. :(&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;H3 **SMURF**?MARGIN: 12pt 0in 3pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Taelosian History &lt;BR&gt;&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold?&gt;-- excerpts taken from the diary of the lost adventurer Vahlar&lt;xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" &gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/H3&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;A Time of Peace&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;This undiscovered continent lied west of Odus.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;It has been passed by all who sail in the &lt;xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" &gt;&lt;st1:place w:st="on"&gt;&lt;st1:PlaceName w:st="on"&gt;Abysmal&lt;/st1:PlaceName&gt; &lt;st1:PlaceType w:st="on"&gt;Sea&lt;/st1:PlaceType&gt;&lt;/st1:place&gt; as it is at the heart of very strong currents.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Until now, no one has gotten close enough to the continent to see it.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;However, with the guidance of Calliav and the Grozmok Stone, the Wayfarers Brotherhood ship -- Queen of Thorns -- forced their ship to land near the continent of Taelosia.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;It is unknown how long Taelosia and its natives have been in existence, but they certainly have had a prolonged presence, much like all of Norrath and its races.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Those I've encountered, however, believe they were not created by any god.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They evolved.&lt;BR **SMURF**?mso-special-character: line-break?&gt;&lt;BR **SMURF**?mso-special-character: line-break?&gt;Taelosia is an unforgiving land.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;It is constantly assaulted by heavy winds.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The landmass itself is very rugged, with a lot of craggy rock.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The flora and fauna that survives here is equally rugged.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The harsh terrain and environment worked in unison to instill two prime beliefs in the people of Taelosia:&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Nothing can escape the ocean’s destructive grasp and the ocean will always provide them with life and plenty of nourishment. The Taelosians began as a peaceful, nature-loving race.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;In the beginning, the city was named Talosi. The Taelosians all lightly gave thanks to the sea and nature for giving them life.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;They were a simple and loving people.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Period of Prayer&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;In 3086, as my best guess, it was determined by a self-ordained high priest of Taelosia, named Ikkibi Daluda, that it was really a sea god named Trushar who was responsible for all the good that happened to the Taelosians.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Over time, several Taelosians followed Ikkibi with fervor.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Others shied away from him. It sounds like anyone not part of the religious tribe came to be known as Nihil.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Over many years, the depth and passion of the religious Taelosians became overzealous.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They began sacrificing their own brethren to the sea in order to please the ocean god Trushar, who apparently wasn't listening for their prayers for calmer winds, seas, and skies. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The Great Separation&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Then, in 3102 or so, in a secret meeting, the High Council of Talosi consisting primarily of Nihil, decided that they didn't want to see their brothers and sisters, mothers and fathers, thrown from the cliffs to the ocean by the religious Taelosians.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They all agreed that the religious tribe should be escorted up to the temples in the mountains. They were to be exiled.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The religious Taelosians believed that the decision was the right one.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Being around the heathens that chose to ignore Trushar could bring wrath upon the city, so they left, willingly.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;As they left, they promised to pray for the destruction of the Nihil from the mountaintops so that Taelosia would be free of the ungrateful.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;A Second Beginning&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Once the religious Taelosians left, the city was renamed, Nihilia. The Nihil went about their peaceful lives once again, relishing their mortal existence.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They converted all of the religious areas into places of celebration and community.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The religious Taelosians eventually became known as the Trusik Tribe.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They prayed incessantly, but not out of love for their god.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They prayed for the destruction of the Nihil and anything that did not believe in a higher power. They continued to build on top of older temples and ruins in the mountains.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Over the years, the rituals and rites the Trusik created to call to the gods became increasingly powerful—so much so that the call was heard beyond the mortal planes of Norrath.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Trusik Transcendence&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The leader of a great army in the Realm of Discord, Mata Muram, heard the call of the Trusik and chose to invade the world the Trusik called from to see what type of creature had a magic that could transcend the boundaries of planes and planets. Mata Muram wanted to learn more about them to see if he could use them in his army to fight for his struggle for power within the Realm of Discord.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Hours of Slaughter&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;On or about 3163, a portal from a far off world was opened by a force that existed in the growing Realm of Discord. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The portal was a tear in space that opened up at the temples in the mountain peaks in Taelosia.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;One of the legion's enslavement expeditionary assault forces poured onto the continent, led by one of many Mata Muram enslavers, Tunat'Muram Cuu Vauax. This arm of the legion is an assault force that is composed of several races.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Each race is unlike anything seen in Norrath.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They are a horrific blend of humanoids, mounts, and other trained beasts.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They all bear the mark of Mata Muram.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The Legion of Mata Muram quickly cut through the ranks of the Taelosians, both the Trusik Tribe at the top of the highest mountains in their temples and down into the city of &lt;st1:place w:st="on"&gt;&lt;st1:City w:st="on"&gt;Nihilia&lt;/st1:City&gt;&lt;/st1:place&gt; where the Nihil lived.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The capacity of the legion to do violence was and is unreal, placing most of the natives into a mass state of shock.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Nothing could be done to stop the wave of chaos that poured through their mountain temples, no matter what they tried.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;They all accepted that they are at the mercy of the legion and its will.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;As soon as the initial wave of troops secured the area, slavers followed behind securing prisoners and herding them back through the portal to serve as slave labor and sacrifices. &lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;Many of the Trusik and Nihil were taken at this time, if they weren't killed.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Break of the Great Tear&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Six days after the initial invasion, the Legion of Mata Muram dominated the populated areas.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The efficiency of their attacks revealed years of experience in similar battles.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Then, the portal became unstable.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;In the Realm of Discord, something changed and the magic that sustained the portal to Norrath imploded, causing a wave of chaotic magic to sweep hundreds of miles in every direction in Norrath.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;At its epicenter, the shockwave wilts and changes everything it hits, turning the land into a twisted shadow of itself.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The Legion of Mata Muram is less affected by the corruption of the magic, but still suffers heavy losses.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;I think this shockwave of magic is evidenced by stones and gems and other earthen materials that carry strange magical properties that began to be unearthed by the Wayfarers Brotherhood in the lost dungeons.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The shockwave also produced another event: several tremendous earthquakes forced massive regions of the continent to collapse.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;As the landmass became unstable, the waves and strong currents that are naturally drawn towards the continent, quickly envelope most of the land.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Norrathians beyond Taelosia were unaware that the event even transpired.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;And while many of the invaders were destroyed during the portal’s implosion, those that remained continued to hunt, torture, and enslave the Taelosians until they could return home to the Realm of Discord.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Enslavement and Awaiting Reentry&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The Taelosians and their stone workers were put to work soon after the loss of the portal back into the Realm of Discord.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;The remaining legion tried to use the Taelosians to rebuild another portal that would send the legion and their remaining acquired slaves back home.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;But they don't have the magic.&lt;SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;Whatever kept the portal open did not exist in Norrath or in the magic of the legion in Norrath.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The Muramites began to simply wait for the portal to reopen, taking out their frustrations on the Taelosians. Then, as my Nihil friend tells me, on the shores of Natimbi in Taelosia, a boat appeared out of the dark mists -- it was us.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2 **SMURF**?BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000016?&gt;Vahlar&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
